com.ibm.watson.dsm.platform.tuples.storage

Class MemoryTupleStorage

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ibm.watson.dsm.platform.tuples.storage.JDBCTupleStorage
      • com.ibm.watson.dsm.platform.tuples.storage.MemoryTupleStorage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDataStorage<ITupleSetDescriptor,ITupleSet>, IReadOnlyDataStorage<ITupleSetDescriptor,ITupleSet>, IReadOnlyTupleStorage, ITupleStorage

    public class MemoryTupleStorage
extends JDBCTupleStorage
implements ITupleStorage
    Implements memory-based tuple storage using SolidDB in-memory implementation. SolidDB, even when running in memory, needs a port. The port defaults to 1934 but can be set with the property "storage.memory.soliddb.port" property set in DSMProperties or in the system properties. SolidDB needs a license file which is looked for in $DSM_HOME/lib, if DSM_HOME env var is set, or in the current directory.
    Author:
    dawood
